As an official partner of the @festivaldecannes, Brut. is covering #Cannes2025 across all its platforms. This year’s festival runs from May 13 to May 24.
A dentist surrendered after two people died following hair transplant surgeries she had performed on them.

A stampede broke out outside Bengaluru’s Chinnaswamy Stadium as thousands of RCB fans gathered to celebrate the team’s historic IPL win.

11 people lost their lives and at least 47 were injured. All the victims were under 40 and the youngest was just 13.

CM Siddaramaiah said the stadium, built for 35,000, was overwhelmed by over 2-3 lakh people. A magisterial inquiry has been ordered, and Rs 10 lakh aid announced for the families of the deceased.

Actor Hina Khan ties the knot with longtime partner Rocky Jaiswal.

Hina, who rose to fame as Akshara in the popular TV show "Yeh Rishta Kya Kehlata Hai", met Rocky on the sets of the show, where he was working as a supervising producer.

Their friendship gradually blossomed into love, and the couple made their relationship public in 2017.

With Alia Bhatt’s powerful debut at Cannes, L’Oréal Paris sparked conversations — about beauty, about confidence, and most of all, about worth.

India joined the celebration through unforgettable L’Oréal Paris experiences across cities, the red carpet dream came closer to home.
#PostCardsFromCannes #lorealparisindia #cannes2025

Karnataka CM Siddaramaiah confirmed 11 people died and 33 were injured after a stampede broke out on 4 June, when thousands of fans gathered outside Bengaluru’s M Chinnaswamy Stadium to celebrate RCB’s IPL 2025 victory.

Karnataka Governor Thawar Chand Gehlot, CM Siddaramaiah and Deputy CM DK Shivakumar felicitated the players at the Vidhan Soudha, the seat of the state’s legislature and secretariat. The team, led by Rajat Patidar, won their first IPL title after an 18-year wait.

Lakhs of fans thronged the Vidhan Soudha and Chinnaswamy Stadium to catch a glimpse of their favourite players, but due to the overwhelming turnout, the celebrations were shortened.
As soon as RCB won their first IPL title, captain Virat Kohli rushed to hug his wife Anushka Sharma. But how did their love story evolve?
As fans celebrate RCB's big IPL win, here's looking back at #ViratKohli's first interview, 18 years ago.
